		<td valign="top" colspan="2">
			<h1>A LITTLE BIT OF ENGLAND IN THE HEART OF<br />SAN FRANCISCO</h1>
			<p>If you're coming to the City by the Bay and are looking for a hotel that captures the diverse flavor of San Francisco, then you'll relish the old world charm of the distinctive Edward II Inn and Suites.</p>
			<p>Established in 1914, and voted one of the <b>Best Romantic Hotels in San Francisco</b><span class="smtxt">*</span>, this exquisite three-story European-style bed and breakfast inn was a labor of love for the original designers.  Our traditional English d&eacute;cor and a welcoming ambiance is a striking contrast to the large and impersonal downtown hotel.</p>
			<h1 class="subhead">The charm of a quaint bed and breakfast.<br />The amenities of a luxury hotel.</h1>
			<p>With 26 rooms and 4 suites, Edward II Inn and Suites offers <a href="./hotel-rooms.html">hotel accommodations</a> that satisfy every taste.  You'll find <a href="./hotel-services.html">hotel amenities</a> which are typical of a 5 star hotel, including wireless and hard-wired Internet access, a <a href="./hotel-gym.html">fully equipped hotel gym</a>, as well as hair and nail care and soothing massages in the comfort of your own hotel room.</p>
			<p>For relaxation, Edward II has its own pub, complete with darts, chess, Scrabble and cards. Next door, the elegant <a href="http://www.cafemaritimesf.com" target="_blank">Caf&eacute; Maritime</a> serves excellent dinners well past the midnight hour.</p>
			<h1 class="subhead">The location puts you in touch with San Francisco's<br />major attractions.</h1>
			<p>Situated along bustling Lombard Street, Edward II is just minutes from San Francisco's historic Presidio and Fort Mason. We're close to Fisherman's Wharf and Ghirardelli Square.  The stylish shops of the Marina District and Union Street are also nearby.</p>
			<p>Old World charm. Twenty-first century conveniences. Edward II Inn and Suites makes your visit a truly unforgettable San Francisco experience.</p>
			<br /><br />
			<p class="smtxt">*As seen in Best of City Search 2002-Bay Area</p>
